instruction using github to pull or push
Global setup:

 Set up git
  git config --global user.name "Your Name"
  git config --global user.email lyase.d@gmail.com
      

Next steps:
 creating from scratch ______________________________________________________

  mkdir basephp
  cd basephp
  git init
  touch README
creating from github pull____________________________________________________
git clone git://github.com/lyase/basecontribution.git
working localy on main branch________________________________________________
edit README
   git commit -m 'more  commit'
working locally on new branch will not be pushed to public repo______________
git checkout -b mybranch
edit README
git commit -a


pushing back_________________________________________________________________
only the master branch get pushed
  git remote add origin git@github.com:lyase/basephp.git
  git push -u origin master

  
